    b.arrow([context.state.node, ...memoizer.async_ids()], b.block(statements)))
```

The `async_ids` are the renamed `$0`, `$1` etc. And `context.state.node` is `$$anchor`.

Hmm, but the issue might be more subtle. Let me think about what happens with the `async_body` wrapping.

When Fragment.js does:
```js
if (has_await) {
    return b.block([b.stmt(b.call('$.async_body', b.arrow([], b.block(body), true)))]);
