Let me think about this from the perspective of the Fragment.js change introduced by commit a60995abe. The change was:

```js
// Before:
const unsuspend = b.id('$$unsuspend');
...
if (has_await) {
    body.push(b.var(unsuspend, b.call('$.suspend')));
}
body.push(...state.consts);
if (has_await) {
    body.push(b.if(b.call('$.aborted'), b.return()));
}
...
